import numpy as np

def CountEq_LargestEq(country):
    temp = Sig_Eqs.loc[Sig_Eqs['Country'] == country]
    count = temp["Country"].count()
    max_Mag = temp['Mag'].max()
    data = temp.loc[temp['Mag'] == max_Mag]
    date = data['Year'].fillna(0).astype(int).astype(str) + "/" + data['Mo'].fillna(0).astype(int).astype(str) + "/" + data['Dy'].fillna(0).astype(int).astype(str)
    return count, list(date)

count, date = CountEq_LargestEq("AZERBAIJAN")
countries = Sig_Eqs['Country'].unique()[1:]
countries = list(countries)
res = []
for country in countries:
    new = []
    count, date = CountEq_LargestEq(country)
    new.append(country)
    new.append(count)
    new.append(date)
    res.append(new)
df = pd.DataFrame(res, columns=["country", "total", "date"])
df.sort_values("total", ascending=False).set_index('country')

2. Wind speed in Shenzhen during the past 10 years (10/10)¶

That's correct for df_mean dataframe, and it is also correct to avoid the effect of 9999 values in wind speed rate by using .count and .sum. But I think it is not necessary to plot monthly variations in each year. Instead, just a overview of ten-year variations would be nice enough. I also see your explnation in report, that's good. Anyway, good job and no point would be deducted.

df['WOda'] = df['WND'].apply(lambda x: x.split(',')[0])  
df['WOdaqc'] = df['WND'].apply(lambda x: x.split(',')[1]) 
df['WOtc'] = df['WND'].apply(lambda x: x.split(',')[2]) 
df['WOsr'] = df['WND'].apply(lambda x: x.split(',')[3]).astype(int)
df['WOsqc'] = df['WND'].apply(lambda x: x.split(',')[4]).astype(int)
df['Year-Month'] = df['DATE'].apply(lambda x: x.split('-')[0]+x.split('-')[1]) 
df_count = df.loc[df['WOsqc'] < 2].groupby('Year-Month')['WOsr'].count()
df_speed = df.loc[df['WOsqc'] < 2].groupby('Year-Month')['WOsr'].sum()
df_mean = (df_speed / df_count) * 0.1
df_mean = pd.DataFrame(df_mean)
